means: 赶紧避开，畏缩( wince的现在分词 )

sentence.Network_cn: 他几乎能感觉到她在电话那端皱眉蹙额。

sentence.Network_en: She switched on the light, wincing at the sudden brightness.
sentence.Network_cn: 她打开了灯, 突如其来的强烈光线刺得她不敢睜眼.

sentence.Network_en: " I will take anything, " he said, relieved, and wincing under reproof.
sentence.Network_cn: “ 我什么事都愿意做, " 他说, 松了一口气, 缩着头等着挨骂.

entry.tran: (因疼痛或因看到、听到或记起不快之事而)皱起脸，皱眉蹙额
entry.def: If you wince, the muscles of your face tighten suddenly because you have felt a pain or because you have just seen, heard, or remembered something unpleasant.

example.ex: Every time he put any weight on his left leg he winced in pain...
example.tran: 只要左腿一受力，他就会疼得龇牙咧嘴。

example.ex: He winced at the thought of dining with Camilla...
example.tran: 一想到要跟卡米拉一起吃饭，他皱起了眉头。
